product_description.Compact and Portable: The powerful interior and portable exterior make the ASUS VivoBook 15 an ideal laptop for work and play. Furthermore, its NanoEdge display along with a matte anti-glare coating ensures an engaging viewing experience.
product_description.Efficient Performance: A cutting-edge, powerful processor ensures that this ASUS laptop delivers lag-free, smooth performance while working, playing, or enjoying entertainment.
product_description.Storage Capacity: The storage capacity offers both high-speed data performance and ample storage capacity. So, you can download, install, and load apps in no time. Also, you can store music, photos, videos, and much more on this laptop.
product_description.Wide View: The NanoEdge Display of this laptop offers an immersive experience while working or playing. Furthermore, the wide-view FHD panel has an anti-glare coating. As a result, you see distraction-free visuals without reflections and glares.
product_description.Lightweight and Portable: This 1.8 kg laptop is easily portable, so you can carry it along wherever you want.
product_description.Touch to Login: This ASUS laptop comes with a built-in fingerprint sensor on its touchpad along with Windows Hello. So, you do not have to type a password to log in.

review: It's good, specially best for students. But the battery backup and camera quality is not so good. And not for gaming like gta 5, bgmi, free fire. If you are a professional gamer then see other laptop.

Writing review after thoroughly usage:

1.Best part is SSD, boot time and performance are quick due to inbuilt SSD.
2. Fingerprint scanner is too fast to unlock.
3. It is lite weight & Design is good inspite of 15.6inch display.
4. Battery backup is 5-6 hours of continuous use.

Worst things in this model that can not be ignored are;

1. Camera is useless, not good for regular use.
2. This model promises UHD display but this is not perfect UHD.
3. Speaker is not impressive and having lower volume due to position of speaker.

Overall the product is good buy except the Camera, UHD & Speaker quality.

It would be a good buy If display size and camera are not an issue.
Fast boot up, good design, cam is poor, good display, fingerprint access, 512ssd and 32optane with 4gb makes a fast boot up

Except camera everything is very good, still 5 star because in this price range for me this is the best laptop.
It has 2 slots for memory so it is upgradable in future and one more thing in the product description nothing is specified about the battery life, but battery life is also very good.
Any one who is looking for productive work can go for it easily (Just keep one thing in mind that camera quality is not good)

I'm writing this review after 7 days of using it.
1)The package was well packed and delivered on time.
2)The booting time of the laptop is about 2-3 seconds.
3)The speed is very good for an average daily tasks(I've uploaded an image where you can see that I was running all the necessity apps and judge by yourself by looking at the graph of cpu performance)
4)The fingerprint works like a charm, it's so quick and fast, in an instant.
5)It's already pre-loaded with basic features/apps including Windows 10(lifetime) which is upgradable to windows 11.

Besides all these many unsaid positive feedbacks I'd like to mention some few cons which might help you decide for the best product.
1)The no. one drawback could be it's battery, though it charge very fast(like in 1&1/2 hours) it drain quick too when in heavy task mode(like 3-4 hours). But it last very long when it's not in heavy task.
2) Don't ever expect to use the webcam. If webcam is your priority you can still go for this and add external webcam.
3)It lack keyboard backlight.
Overall a good product at the offered price. I spent a good amount of time researching about a decent laptop at my affordable budget and I finally chose this product over others. No regrets. Hope you make the best choice. 😊
